    "id": "nm0000168",
    "name": "Samuel L. Jackson",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQ1NTQwMTYxNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwMjA1MzY1._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "Samuel L. Jackson is an American producer and highly prolific actor, having appeared in over 100 films, including , , , , , , and the Star Wars prequel trilogy (1999-2005), as well as the Marvel Cinematic Universe.Samuel Leroy Jackson was born in Washington, D.C., to Elizabeth (Montgomery) and Roy Henry Jackson. He was raised by his mother, a factory worker, and his grandparents. At Morehouse College, Jackson was active in the black student movement. In the seventies, he joined the Negro Ensemble Company (together with ). In the eighties, he became well-known after three movies made by : , and . He achieved prominence and critical acclaim in the early 1990s with films such as , , , , and his collaborations with director , including , , and later . Going from supporting player to leading man, his performance in gave him an Oscar nomination for his character Jules Winnfield, and he received a Silver Berlin Bear for his part as Ordell Robbi in . Jackson usually played bad guys and drug addicts before becoming an action hero, co-starring with in and in .With Jackson's permission, his likeness was used for the Ultimate version of the Marvel Comics character, Nick Fury. He later did a cameo as the character in a post-credits scene from , and went on to sign a nine-film commitment to reprise this role in future films, including major roles in , , and and minor roles in and . He has also portrayed the character in the second and final episodes of the first season of the TV show, Marvel's . He has provided his voice to several animated films, television series and video games, including the roles of Lucius Best / Frozone in Pixar's film , Mace Windu in , Afro Samurai in the anime television series , and Frank Tenpenny in the video game .",
