    "id": "nm0000906",
    "name": "Annette Bening",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTc4ODQ1ODM5Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwOTU2NDk3OQ@@._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "Annette Bening was born on May 29, 1958 in Topeka, Kansas, the youngest of four children. Her family moved to California when she was young, and she grew up there. She graduated from San Francisco State University and began her acting career with the American Conservatory Theatre in San Francisco, eventually moving to New York where she acted on the stage (including a Tony-award nomination in 1987 for her work in the Broadway play \"Coastal Disturbances\") and got her first film roles, in a few TV movies.As is so often the case, her first big-screen role was in a forgettable movie, this one , in which she had little screen time. However, her next work onscreen was in 's , a film adaptation of ' \"Les Liaisons Dangereuses\". Unfortunately, de Laclos' story had also just served as the source of a more Hollywoodized and successful movie version, , which had been released the previous year, and Foreman's treatment went little noticed. Bening's career turned an important corner the following year when she co-starred with and in 's powerful, entertaining screen adaptation of 's novel , and her artful turn as a con artist gained her the first of several Academy award nominations. On the strength of this performance cast Bening as , 's fiery actress moll, in his , the story of Siegel's founding of Las Vegas. Although the movie itself did not fare well, it resulted in a relationship with Beatty which led to Bening's pregnancy and then her marriage to Beatty in 1992 - it was the second marriage for Bening, who had been separated from her first husband since 1986 but did not finalize her divorce until 1991. The couple then collaborated on the extravagant flop , though the next year her career rebounded with her turn as Queen Elizabeth in the highly-regarded 1995 production of . Notable performances have since included an obsessive, pushy real estate agent in , and as the eponymous character in 's screen adaptation of the novel - both were duly noted by the Academy, with Oscar nominations.Bening has great poise and screen presence and, at her best, can turn in a very strong performance. Although her resume often features long stretches of mediocre productions before the next good part turns up, when it does, it proves worth the wait. Bening has four children with Beatty.",
    "birthDate": null,
    "birthPlace": "Topeka, Kansas",
    "knownFor": [
      "American Beauty"
    ]
