    "bio": "Sally Margaret Field was born November 6, 1946 in Pasadena, California, to actress (née Morlan) and salesman Richard Dryden Field. Her parents divorced in 1950 and her mother then married stuntman , and they had a daughter, . She also has a brother, Richard Field. Sally attended Birmingham High School in Van Nuys, California.Her acting career began in 1965, when she landed the role of Frances Elizabeth 'Gidget' Lawrence in ; it was canceled after only one season because of bad ratings. She went on to star in , which ran for three seasons. She also appeared in her first film in 1967, opposite . In the next few years she appeared in numerous TV movies and TV shows such as , , , and . In 1977 she starred alongside then-boyfriend in the box office hit , which led to a less successful sequel in 1980. In 1979 she starred in the popular film and she received her first Oscar for that role.In the years that followed she starred in films such as , , (she received her second Oscar for her role), , and . In 1993 she starred alongside and in the popular comedy . A year after, she played the role of character's mother (even though she's only ten years older than he is in real life) in . The film was a huge commercial success and won six Academy awards.Since then she has appeared in TV movies and miniseries such as , , and . In 2000 she appeared in the film with and , and in 2003 she starred alongside in . She also appeared in 12 episodes of from 2000 to 2006. From 2006 to 2011, she played the role of matriarch Nora Walker in the hit television show , which earned her an Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series. Getting back into film, she earned her third Oscar nomination for and played Aunt May in and its blockbuster sequel.Sally has been married twice, first to Steven Craig from 1968 to 1973. They had two sons together, and . Her second marriage was to film producer from 1984 to 1994. They had one son together, Samuel Greisman. Between marriages, from 1976 to 1980, she was in a relationship with .",
