    "id": "nm3154303",
    "name": "Timothée Chalamet",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTIyZWY4ZjktOGJiZi00NGFkLTllMjctZjJjMmNiMjIxOTY2XkEyXkFqcGc@._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "Timothée Hal Chalamet was born in Manhattan, to , a real estate broker and dancer, and Marc Chalamet, a UNICEF editor. His mother, who is from New York, is Jewish, and of Russian Jewish and Polish Jewish descent. His father, who is from Nîmes, France, is of French and English ancestry. He is the brother of actress , a nephew of director , and a grandson of screenwriter .He grew up in an artistic family, appearing in commercials and the New York theatre scene, and attending the LaGuardia High School of Music, Art and Performing Arts, where his classmate and friend was actor (the two later received their first Golden Globe nominations in the same year, 2017). For a time, Timothée also attended Columbia University.He made his film debut in 2014, as a high school student in 's and 's character's teenage son in . He subsequently had sizable roles in several indie films, playing the younger version of writer Stephen Elliott in , the male lead, Zac, in the drama , and Billy in the road trip drama . On stage, he has appeared in the plays The Talls, by , and 's autobiographical Prodigal Son, while on television, he has had a minor role in the film , a big part in , and meatier roles on the shows and , among other work.He broke out in 2017, appearing in notable supporting roles, as a soldier in the western and a high school crush of the title character in , and in a leading role as Elio, an Italian Jewish 17-year-old who romances his father's older assistant, played by , in the drama . Timothée's role as Elio received significant critical acclaim, and he was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Actor, the Golden Globe Award for Best Actor, Drama, and won many critics' groups' awards for Best Actor of the Year.In 2018, he starred as Nic Sheff, who suffers from substance abuse problems, in the drama . In 2019, he headlined the comedy , with , played Henry V of England, King from 1413 to 1422, in the historical drama , and embodied love interest Laurie in Greta Gerwig's take on .",
