    "id": "nm0001001",
    "name": "James Caan",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTI5NjkyNDQ3NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNjY5NTQ0Mw@@._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "A masculine and enigmatic actor whose life and movie career have had more ups and downs than the average rollercoaster and whose selection of roles has arguably derailed him from achieving true superstar status, James Caan is New York-born and bred.He was born in the Bronx, to Sophie (Falkenstein) and Arthur Caan, Jewish immigrants from Germany. His father was a meat dealer and butcher. The athletically gifted Caan played football at Michigan State University while studying economics, holds a black belt in karate and for several years was even a regular on the rodeo circuit, where he was nicknamed \"The Jewish Cowboy\". However, while studying at Hofstra University, he became intrigued by acting and was interviewed and accepted at 's Neighborhood Playhouse. He then won a scholarship to study under acting coach and began to appear in several off-Broadway productions, including \"I Roam\" and \"Mandingo\".He made his screen debut as a sailor in and began to impress audiences with his work in and the western alongside and . Further work followed in and in the sensitive . However, audiences were moved to tears as he put in a heart-rending performance as cancer-stricken Chicago Bears running back Brian Piccolo in the highly rated made-for-TV film .With these strong performances under his belt, then cast him as hot-tempered gangster Santino \"Sonny\" Corleone in the Mafia epic . The film was an enormous success, Caan scored a Best Supporting Actor nomination and, in the years since, the role has proven to be the one most fondly remembered by his legion of fans. He reprised the role for several flashback scenes in the sequel and then moved on to several very diverse projects. These included a cop-buddy crime partnership with in the uneven , a superb performance as a man playing for his life in alongside , and pairing with in . Two further strong lead roles came up for him in 1975, first as futuristic sports star \"Jonathon E\" questioning the moral fiber of a sterile society in and teaming up with in the spy thriller .Unfortunately, Caan's rising star sputtered badly at this stage of his career, and several film projects failed to find fire with either critics or audiences. These included such failures as the hokey , the quasi-western and the saccharine . However, he did score again with the stylish -directed heist movie . He followed this with a supernatural romantic comedy titled and then, due to personal conflicts, dropped out of the spotlight for several years before returning with a stellar performance under old friend Francis Ford Coppola in the moving .Caan appeared back in favor with fans and critics alike and raised his visibility with the sci-fi hit and , then surprised everyone by playing a meek romance novelist held captive after a car accident by a deranged fan in the dynamic . The 1990s were kind to him and he notched up roles as a band leader in , another gangster in , appeared in the indie hit and pursued in .The demand on Caan's talents seems to have increased steadily over the past few years as he is making himself known to a new generation of fans. Recent hot onscreen roles have included , and . In addition, he finds himself at the helm of the hit TV series as casino security chief \"Big Ed\" Deline. An actor of undeniably manly appeal, James Caan continued to surprise and delight audiences with his invigorating performances up until his death in July 2022 at the age of 82.",
    "birthDate": null,
    "birthPlace": "the Bronx, to Sophie (Falkenstein) and Arthur Caan",
    "knownFor": [
      "Thief"
    ]
