    "id": "nm0000443",
    "name": "Goldie Hawn",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTc0MDQ5MDUzMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjIwNTU5MTE@._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "Goldie Jeanne Hawn was born November 21, 1945 in Washington, D.C. to , who owned a dance school, and , a band musician. She has one sister, entertainment publicist ; a brother, Edward, died in infancy before her birth. She was raised in the Jewish religion. Her mother was Jewish and the daughter of Hungarian immigrants. Her father was Presbyterian. At the age of three, Goldie began taking ballet and tap dance lessons, and at the age of ten she danced in the chorus of the Ballet Russe de Monte Carlo production of \"The Nutcracker\". At the age of 19 she ran and instructed a ballet school, having dropped out of college where she was majoring in drama. Before going into the film business she worked as a professional dancer.Hawn made her feature film debut in , with a small role as a giggling dancer. Her first big role came in 1969, where she played opposite and in , a role which earned her an Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress. After the Oscar win her career took off and she followed with roles in successful comedies such as and , and more dramatic roles in and . In 1978, she starred alongside in the box office hit, . In 1980 she starred in another box office hit, , where she also served as producer. During the 1980s she starred in hit movies such as , and . In 1987, she appeared with her boyfriend in , which became both a critical and box office disappointment. Her career slowed down after that until 1990 when she starred alongside in . In 1992 she starred in the successful film, , with and , which was followed by another successful film , which co-starred . In 1996 she played the role of an aging alcoholic actress in the comedy, , with and ; it became a critical and financial success. She also starred in the film and , which reunited her with Martin. In 2001 and 2002 she starred in with , and with .Goldie has been married twice. First to dancer/director from 1969 to 1973. In 1976 she married musician and became a mother for the first time that year, when she gave birth to their son . In 1979, she had her second child with Hudson, daughter . The marriage ended in divorce in 1980. Since 1983, she has been having a relationship with actor . Their son was born in 1986. Goldie is also a de-facto stepmother to Kurt's son . She has eight grandchildren.",
