    "id": "nm0177896",
    "name": "Bradley Cooper",
    "photo": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2YwYjg4NjItZGFjNC00NzgzLWJhMTktYTZmODlmM2Y4ODJjXkEyXkFqcGc@._V1_.jpg",
    "bio": "Bradley Charles Cooper was born on January 5, 1975 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. His mother, Gloria (Campano), is of Italian descent, and worked for a local NBC station. His father, Charles John Cooper, who was of Irish descent, was a stockbroker. Immediately after Bradley graduated from the Honors English program at Georgetown University in 1997, he moved to New York City to enroll in the Masters of Fine Arts program at the Actors Studio Drama School at New School University. There, he developed his stage work, culminating with his thesis performance as John Merrick in 's \"The Elephant Man\", performed in New York's Circle in the Square.While still in school, Bradley began his professional career, appearing opposite on and on the drama series . His weekends were spent with LEAP (Learning through the Expanded Arts Program), a non-profit organization that teaches acting and movement to inner city school children. The summers took him all across the globe, from kayaking in British Columbia with Orca Whales to ice-climbing in the Peruvian Andes, while hosting Lonely Planet's for the Discovery Channel. Bradley had to miss his graduation ceremony from the Actors Studio in order to star in his first feature . After finishing his second feature , his plans to relocate to Los Angeles were delayed when hired him to star on the drama series .Bradley went on to win the role of young law student Gordon Pinella in , starring and , and also played Travis Paterson in . He finally decided that it was time to forgo his other New York projects and move to Los Angeles when he was cast on . After supporting roles in , , , and , Cooper broke out with major roles in , and . He co-starred in the action film and headlined the thriller film .Cooper received an Academy Award nomination for Best Actor after starring opposite in 's . He then received two more consecutive Oscar nominations, Best Supporting Actor for playing Richie DiMaso in Russell's (again opposite Lawrence, though their characters shared no significant screen time), and Best Actor for playing Navy SEAL Chris Kyle in 's , the highest grossing film of 2014. During this time period, Cooper also reprised his role in and , turned in another strong dramatic turn in , and voiced Rocket Raccoon in the third highest grossing film of 2014, .In 2015, Bradley headlined two comedies, 's , set in Hawaii, and ' , set in London, and starred opposite Jennifer Lawrence again in David O. Russell's .Bradley has a daughter (born 2017) with his former partner, model .",
    "birthDate": null,
    "birthPlace": "Philadelphia, Pennsylvania",
    "knownFor": [
      "A Star Is Born"
    ]
